# Wolf Den — example hand-drawn map (Earth / Normal1, see EncounterRegistry).
# File rows read top-to-bottom as far-edge-to-near-edge: the first grid row below is the
# FAR side of the battlefield (z = HEIGHT-1, where enemies stand), the last grid row is the
# NEAR side (z = 0, the player's side) — so this file reads the same way the map looks.
# Columns read left-to-right as x = 0..WIDTH-1.
#
# See MapCodeTables.cs for the full code list.

WIDTH=8
HEIGHT=8

